					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Brad on the SoV and more</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=292576" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037021.html">Scars of Velious in stores Tomorrow</a></B><P>

As usual though, all the new content is for the high level crowd. What about the poor slobs that only have a couple hours a week, and are only 24th even though they have been playing a year?<P>

<B>Tiervalen: Essentially, the majority of our player base is heading into their 30s, and with the backstory of Velious describing it as a pretty nasty and exotic place, we decided to make the expansion targetted for levels 35-60.<P>

One could also argue that new players and casual players (for the sake of argument, those below 35 I suppose) still, by definition, have tons of already existing content to explore and devour.<P>

All that said, I definitely hear what you're saying and it's also a concern on our part (we definitely want to provide new content for ALL EQ players, new or old, casual or hard core, RPers or power gamers) To that end, we've both short and long term goals:<P>

We still have quite a few dungeons to revamp, and those include low, mid and high (including the planes). With Velious in stores tomorrow, you'll see the Expansion and Live teams move on pretty quickly to these revamps (although there will undoubtedly be some clean up and we do have the holidays approaching). <P>

Also, I'd like to see at least one (perhaps two) new free zones launch during 2001, and I think we should focus on low to mid levels.<P>

And lastly, should there be another expansion post-Velious (and while I'm certainly not announcing anything... well, with 310,000 subscribers and growing, I see a long future ahead of EQ :), we'll most likely target all levels (1-60), similar to what we did with Kunark.<P>

-Brad</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

If Scars of Velious is on sale tomorrow then it is live ? <P>

<B>Yes, it's been live since around noon today. We always need to be ready should some retailers break the street date.<P>

-Brad</B><P>

For someone whos bandwith cost is based off the Maximum bandiwth required, I am completely boggled at your lack of internationl support for those "off peak hours" where "filling the pipes" can only be advantageous for you and your back pocket. <P>

For an online game where "first in best dressed" tends to apply for the goodies, I am dissapointed at your casual attitude to your international (non-US based) customers.<P>

<B>Drizz_TT: I definitely understand your concerns and believe me, I'd love to have boxes everywhere in the world tomorrow morning.<P>

It's easier said than done, though, and international distribution can be tricky. Essentially, it involves a lot of other parties, contracts, etc.<P>

That said, with excellent partners (for example, UBIsoft in Europe), we've been doing a LOT better recently, and I hope to see Velious everywhere in short order.<P>

In the meantime, I appreciate your loyalty to the game and desire to play -- making sure you get a copy ASAP is something beneficial to both of us, I assure you :)<P>

-Brad</B><P>

<B>Guys, thank you for all the feedback. I'd really thought international distribution would be faster for Velious, but apparently for many of you its not.<P>

I apologize.<P>

I will meet with our VP of Sales today and see if anything can be done.<P>

-Brad</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037337.html">Velious International Distribution Update</a></B><P>

<I>Velious International Distribution Update<P>

EverQuest: The Scars of Velious should be in stores across Europe Dec 14th next Thursday.<P>

I'm still waiting for news on availability elsewhere (Asia, etc.) and will post again when I have news.<P>

-Brad</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037080.html">Why is MIP MAPPING still broken?</a></B><P>

Any one have an idea as to why MIP MAPPING is still not working on Charater Models in the game? It worked great up to patch on 11-29-00 but now the Charaters in the game look awful.<P>

<B>With the last patch (or maybe the one before that), we decided to turn off mip mapping for everything but the world (in other words, it's not on for characters and objects).<P>

We did this because mip mapping all those textures was causing performance problems and pauses for many players. That, and we really think subjectively that the advantages of mip mapping are for the most part apparent and beneficial only on world geometry.<P>

That said, you seem to disagree. We'd love to hear some other feedback on this. Perhaps we could provide several options (for example, no mip mapping, mip mapping world only, mip mapping all textures) were there a demand. <P>

Let us know, and maybe Rowyl can look into it and let us know if such options are possible.<P>

-Brad</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037322.html">Brad, what about The Warrens?!</a></B><P>

You sound like you'd LIKE to see at least one, but you don't have any definite plans...I thought The Warrens (a hopefully Blackburrow-type dungeon for lowbies) was supposed to have been out ALREADY.<P>

<B>Warrens will indeed be the first, and hopefully we'll be able to do a second.<P>

Once we know more of what our plans for 2001, we'll let you know. Right now the team is still recovering from many, many late nights working on Velious :)<P>

-Brad</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
